---
import SiteLayout from "../components/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Astropress Admin Model"
  description="Astropress treats the admin as the product surface for editors, not as a sidecar to a static site generator."
  heading="The admin is the center of the editing workflow."
  currentPath="/admin"
>
  <section class="panel-grid">
    <article class="panel">
      <h2>Editor workflow</h2>
      <p>
        Editors work in the admin to create, review, schedule, revise, and publish content. They do not need Git to
        do normal editorial work.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="panel">
      <h2>Core surfaces</h2>
      <p>
        Pages, posts, media, redirects, comments, users, translations, settings, and revisions are all intended to be
        managed from one bounded admin surface.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="panel">
      <h2>Provider neutrality</h2>
      <p>
        Editors should not have to learn provider-specific runtime differences just to update content. Adapters absorb
        those differences behind stable contracts.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="panel">
    <h2>What Astropress is trying to avoid</h2>
    <p>
      The project is intentionally not drifting toward a universal website builder. The goal is a simpler, more
      operable publishing app for clearly bounded sites.
    </p>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
